transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, I'm calling because I paid for Viagra AGV, which I was told was made by the makers

Speaker 2: of Viagra, and I was shipped just generic Sildenafil, which doesn't, and I tried one

Speaker 1: pill and it doesn't work.

Speaker 2: Now I have other generic Sildenafil.

Speaker 1: I also wrote into customer service, so I want my money back.

Speaker 2: I want the Viagra AGV shipped to me, or I want my money back.

Speaker 1: Okay, let me pull you up so I can see what's going on.

Speaker 2: Can I have your name and birthday?

Speaker 1: Yep, my name is Frank Dougherty, D-O-U-G-H-E-R-T-Y, and my birth date is 12-5-1958.

Speaker 2: Okay, and Concord, are you still on Concord Street?

Speaker 1: Yep.

Speaker 2: Okay, I'm going to have the AGV sent out to you today.

Speaker 1: Give me a second, you've got 100 milligrams, 40...

Speaker 2: Again?

Speaker 1: I'm just verifying your order.

Speaker 2: I'm going to have the AGV shipped out to you today.

Speaker 1: Okay, why would they send me the generic one in the first place?

Speaker 2: Did you do it online?

Speaker 1: I did it online, yep.

Speaker 2: Oh, there must have been a disconnect online.

Speaker 1: Okay, when am I going to receive this?

Speaker 2: You'll get it in like four business days.

Speaker 1: Am I going to get some type of an email that says that they're sending me it?

Speaker 2: That's correct.

Speaker 1: Okay, I'm not getting charged anything else, right?

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: Yes, what?

Speaker 2: No, no, no, you're not getting charged. Yes, you're not getting charged.

Speaker 1: And what am I supposed to do with these junk pills that you sent me in the first place?

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: All right, I'm going to hold you to it, because if not, I'm going to put a stop payment.

Speaker 2: Okay, no problem.

Speaker 1: With Bank of America, okay?

Speaker 2: When am I going to get that email?

Speaker 1: Documenting this phone call.

Speaker 2: You'll get the email within a couple of minutes.

Speaker 1: A couple of minutes, and what is your name, just in case I don't, so I can prove...

Speaker 2: Summer?

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: Like spelling like summer?

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: It's 3:15 here, so I'm assuming it's what, 12:15 your time?

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: You know, I went online and looked up your company in the Better Business Bureau,

Speaker 1: and like 90% of the complaints are for this exact same thing.

Speaker 2: Okay, no problem.

Speaker 1: You'll get the email.

Speaker 2: It's because you did it online.

Speaker 1: There was a disconnect.

Speaker 2: I've shipped out the AGV to you.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Okay, have a good day.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.

Speaker 2: Thank you.
